[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring serialization options**\n\nI'm considering whether I can use a public API to load a serialized object from a pre-existing stream as a resource. I need to figure out if it's acceptable to incorporate a base64 serialized JCEDHPrivateKey crafted externally. Since it uses standard serialization without requiring metadata edits, maybe I could hardcode a byte array for base64. Deserialization would then trigger readObject, while reserialization would focus on writeObject. It's a bit of a puzzle, but I think I'm on the right track!\n\n**Considering BigInteger serialization**\n\nI’m looking into the current JDK's BigInteger and thinking about its serialization. It seems like the key fields are serialPersistentFields: {signum, magnitude}, but I notice that serialVersionUID is stable. That should help with consistent serialization during streaming. I think it’s manageable, but I wonder if there are nuances that might affect performance. There’s a lot to consider in the context of ensuring accuracy and efficiency when working with such data types!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00ef1a1265e5b4db016a10d7014274819e89eb5f9974ef7119\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqENcUP7vr0xgkMTNcBw16Ua2Bm4e9iVSaPVlK8hqQylldoXHClShb0uLUJ5lJsCKWmAbWjd9JJ3En4bZv4PiC3Pp2ymJv2bIRYypufWEKF52-FPcfAIQLhLqw871mf_4dtZB_pEBx2_x25nCz9ePvlqsS-IczAsQ8QSTnRs1tjZRbjZTdYlyibpdqZWvWafjUWUAyaGMkmz0PhFztU8k7GQHctMy-CmrD0-JFb0bdrlTuO-uUxfTzoVo3Y_OFY1dunwME6c_jUV6vzV8rtHAGBLwMtoc9DRZe6YUiFONhmcFa3fkGLsrnKbSCrxw6z0DMMpNKUGXqWrfEpe-m1BnG-6ksUjmacxYqhY5LV9o2VnLNBxVw6LwtyYnYBCmFJKW-ZgXHgNDOEKxRgvkyEs6SqYDALL3VCNyH6SLKwMePL8IJr-bLQD3UYVZlXWhEfRIgcA0PV_FYB6V2lqqyda_i0kdWqqonMcyjqQLeCyRx0FpG_uCj7YaMegMA_QaWgce2Q0ZFZevn79xB8_1-7ry9p-KCxwbFO_l1UOJlLgNh97ybnY85QXZzwtnDp43gR3YdGGkuvS4bY-BEm2nkeSS4tX3xJNXA4Pyhrqg8EmSjiWShcfzFzFVJUft2oIotlaFzfWtouPz73DHi6rUHMgkVi5taKJ4_uzFFhowT5X6d